Interview Answer
This function acts as a wrapper around the Groq API. It receives conversation messages, sends them to the Llama 3.1 model hosted on Groq, and returns the generated response. The function allows us to control model selection, output token limits, and temperature. Internally, it sends an HTTPS request to Groq servers, where the LLM processes the prompt and returns the generated content. We use this same function throughout the application for summarization, question generation, and RAG-based PDF chat.


